dreaming_meta_recipe
  record_type "meta_recipe"
  topic "dreaming"
  title "Dreaming: low-priority memory maintenance and meta-algorithm self-generalization"
  summary "Machine-readable recipe for the deterministic dreaming system (issue #540). While the core server or desktop shell is truly idle, dreaming follows memory links, derives frequent-topic tasks, learns data-grounded requirements and recurring structures, replays candidate tasks against proposed amendments, retains only verified coverage, applies retained rules to later protocol answers, measures the real filesystem, and — only with persisted consent — forgets recomputable data toward a 20% reserve."
  generalization "Extend dreaming through these thirteen data-grounded stages rather than topic-specific production branches. A new experience participates through durability, links, topic frequency, data cues, candidate replay, and structure mining; only replay-verified coverage permits a specific record to be forgotten, while retained amendments and patterns improve future tasks."
step_classify_durability
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "1"
  id "classify_durability"
  title "Classify every event by how durable and recomputable it is"
  detail "classify_event maps each MemoryEvent to one DreamingDurability: IrreplaceableRaw user/assistant/system experience, RetainedLearning skill ledgers and meta-algorithm amendments, DeletedConversation events on soft-deleted threads, RecomputableCache public-source/tool output, and RecomputableIntermediate summaries and test-run specifics. Only the reclaimable classes are ever eligible to be forgotten, so raw experience and learning are structurally protected."
  source_file "src/dreaming.rs"
step_recalculate_usage
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "2"
  id "recalculate_usage"
  title "Recalculate how often each event is actually used"
  detail "usage_counts recomputes, for every event, how many other events reference its id across their searchable text and evidence. Deduplication and pressure eviction are ordered by this recalculated frequency of use, so the most-reused copy is the one retained (issue #540: restructure deduplication by recalculated frequency of use)."
  source_file "src/dreaming.rs"
step_restructure_duplicates
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "3"
  id "restructure_duplicates"
  title "Restructure recomputable duplicates around the most-reused copy"
  detail "duplicate_key groups recomputable events with identical payloads; the group keeps the copy with the highest recalculated usage and proposes RemoveDuplicateRecomputable for the rest. Duplicates are only ever collapsed among recomputable data, never raw experience or learning."
  source_file "src/dreaming.rs"
step_recalculate_topics
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "4"
  id "recalculate_topics"
  title "Recalculate which topics the user interacts with most"
  detail "event_topic attributes each event to its most specific stable label and learn_from_memory ranks topics by recalculated interaction frequency into TopicFrequency records."
  source_file "src/dreaming/learning.rs"
step_learn_requirements
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "5"
  id "learn_requirements"
  title "Recover the durable requirements the user stated on those topics"
  detail "requirement_statement uses the multilingual cue records in data/meta/dreaming-cues.lino to lift standing requirements from user-authored events; the cues are grounded data, not an English-only production branch."
  source_file "src/dreaming/learning.rs"
step_generalize_amendments
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "6"
  id "generalize_amendments"
  title "Generalize each requirement into a meta-algorithm amendment"
  detail "learn_from_memory proposes one MetaAlgorithmAmendment per frequent topic carrying a durable requirement. The proposal is not yet allowed to claim coverage."
  source_file "src/dreaming/learning.rs"
step_replay_candidates
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "7"
  id "replay_candidates"
  title "Derive candidate tasks and replay the amended meta-algorithm"
  detail "replay_candidate_tasks discovers prior task/test-run records on frequent topics and compares their recorded expected output with the generalized result. amendment_reproduces_specific grants coverage only after an exact normalized replay passes."
  source_file "src/dreaming/learning.rs"
step_mine_patterns
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "8"
  id "mine_patterns"
  title "Mine recurring task structures independent of language cues"
  detail "mine_patterns derives repeated first-token task structures such as refactor * from event data and retains them as dreaming_pattern learning records."
  source_file "src/dreaming/learning.rs"
step_apply_future_tasks
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "9"
  id "apply_future_tasks"
  title "Apply retained amendments to similar future tasks"
  detail "apply_retained_amendments reads structured meta_algorithm_amendment events and changes later OpenAI-compatible chat and responses answers when their topic matches, without requiring the user to repeat the standing rule."
  source_file "src/dreaming_application.rs"
step_reclaim_free_space
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "11"
  id "reclaim_free_space"
  title "Reclaim space toward the 20% free-space reserve"
  detail "required_reclaim_bytes derives the deficit from the target_free_ratio_percent (default 20%, issue #494), current free bytes, and the next incoming write; the pressure phase then selects the lowest-use reclaimable events until the target is met, reporting requires_bigger_storage when recomputable data alone cannot satisfy it. Garbage collection keeps roughly a fifth of memory free by forgetting only recomputable/refetchable data."
  source_file "src/dreaming.rs"
step_forget_covered_specifics
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "12"
  id "forget_covered_specifics"
  title "Forget the specifics a retained amendment can reproduce, keep the amendment"
  detail "Under pressure plan_memory_dreaming prefers ForgetCoveredSpecific: a specific task/test-run record whose id appears in the covered_event_ids that replay_candidate_tasks verified is forgotten before any other recomputable data, because the generalized amendment can reproduce it. The amendment itself is RetainedLearning and never reclaimable, so the general meta algorithm keeps every change that lets it solve the whole task class even after its specifics are gone."
  source_file "src/dreaming.rs"
step_measure_real_storage
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "10"
  id "measure_real_storage"
  title "Measure real storage and the actual incoming write"
  detail "measure_storage asks the filesystem for total and available bytes and plan_for_real_storage includes the actual incoming byte count rather than relying on static defaults."
  source_file "src/storage_policy.rs"
step_idle_consent_runtime
  record_type "meta_step"
  order "13"
  id "idle_consent_runtime"
  title "Run at low priority while idle and require persisted consent to free space"
  detail "run_core_dreaming_once and the desktop scheduler yield to foreground work. Learning may be retained by default, but removal actions run only after the user's auto-free-space choice is persisted; otherwise the system reports a bigger-storage prompt."
  source_file "src/dreaming_runtime.rs"
